WEBVTT

00:00.328 --> 00:03.729
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:03.732 --> 00:08.468
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:08.493 --> 00:11.539
<i>Fellow citizens and compatriots,</i>

00:11.564 --> 00:15.568
<i>I am besieged by 1,000
or more Mexicans</i>

00:15.594 --> 00:17.093
<i>under Santa Anna.</i>

00:17.118 --> 00:19.507
<i>I have sustained a
continual bombardment</i>

00:19.532 --> 00:21.647
<i>and cannonade for 24 hours,</i>

00:21.650 --> 00:23.348
<i>and have not lost a man.</i>

00:23.351 --> 00:24.750
- Hee-ya!
- [horse neighs]

00:24.753 --> 00:25.848
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:25.873 --> 00:28.950
<i>I shall never surrender or retreat.</i>

00:28.975 --> 00:31.215
<i>Then I call on you in the name of liberty,</i>

00:31.240 --> 00:32.458
<i>of patriotism,</i>

00:32.482 --> 00:35.327
<i>and everything dear to
the American character</i>

00:35.330 --> 00:38.764
<i>to come to our aid with all dispatch.</i>

00:38.767 --> 00:42.440
<i>The enemy is receiving
reinforcements daily</i>

00:42.465 --> 00:45.416
<i>and will no doubt increase
to 3,000 or 4,000</i>

00:45.441 --> 00:46.905
<i>in four or five days.</i>

00:46.908 --> 00:49.916
<i>If this call is neglected,</i>

00:49.941 --> 00:52.069
<i>I am determined to sustain myself</i>

00:52.094 --> 00:54.202
<i>as long as possible
and die like a soldier</i>

00:54.227 --> 00:56.615
<i>who never forgets what
is due to his own honor,</i>

00:56.618 --> 00:58.383
<i>and that of his country:</i>

00:58.386 --> 01:00.007
<i>victory...</i>

01:00.032 --> 01:01.102
<i>or death.</i>

01:01.127 --> 01:03.699
<i>Lieutenant Colonel William Barret Travis,</i>

01:03.724 --> 01:05.259
<i>the Alamo.</i>

01:08.296 --> 01:10.429
[footsteps approaching]

01:10.432 --> 01:12.266
You're late.

01:14.569 --> 01:17.636
Is it safe to talk in here?
I mean, are they listening?

01:17.639 --> 01:18.971
What're you prattling on about?

01:18.974 --> 01:21.540
Of course it's safe.

01:21.543 --> 01:24.276
- Ask my why I'm late.
- Why are you late?

01:24.279 --> 01:26.879
Because I don't have a car.
Ask my why I don't have a car.

01:26.882 --> 01:28.413
Because I am too scared to get in mine

01:28.416 --> 01:30.148
because your Rittenhouse guys hacked me

01:30.151 --> 01:32.084
while I was going 50 miles an hour!

01:32.087 --> 01:35.153
- Are you all right?
- Do I look all right?

01:35.178 --> 01:36.524
Right, well, I'm sorry.

01:36.549 --> 01:39.625
They, um, shouldn't be
contacting you directly.

01:39.628 --> 01:41.660
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:41.663 --> 01:43.929
Is that all you have to say?

01:43.932 --> 01:45.564
You sold me out.

01:45.567 --> 01:48.066
You had them send some goon
to threaten me and my family.

01:48.069 --> 01:51.069
Wait a minute. I'd never do that.

01:51.072 --> 01:54.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:54.743 --> 01:57.242
You're like a son to me.

01:57.245 --> 01:59.144
Now, for you to think that I would...

01:59.147 --> 02:02.915
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:02.918 --> 02:06.618
I don't know what to think of you.

02:06.621 --> 02:08.920
Well, now you know
what they're capable of.

02:08.924 --> 02:11.757
You have to cooperate.

02:11.760 --> 02:13.425
We both do.

02:13.428 --> 02:20.434
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:23.104 --> 02:25.437
- You wanted to see me, ma'am?
- Thank you for coming in.

02:25.440 --> 02:26.972
I know it's late.

02:26.975 --> 02:29.141
This is Deputy Director Patrick Ramsey,

02:29.144 --> 02:31.109
my boss at the NCTC.

02:31.112 --> 02:33.946
Master Sergeant Logan, it's an honor.

02:33.949 --> 02:35.380
You're a real war hero.

02:35.383 --> 02:36.949
We've all heard what you did in Syria.

02:36.952 --> 02:39.685
But you're replacing me.

02:39.688 --> 02:42.220
- How'd you know?
- A guy like you doesn't show up

02:42.223 --> 02:44.489
unless it's to get rid of
a guy like me, sir.

02:44.492 --> 02:46.892
The job's to kill Garcia Flynn.

02:46.895 --> 02:49.061
You just haven't gotten it done.

02:49.064 --> 02:51.964
Maybe the next guy will.

02:51.967 --> 02:54.066
- Who're you bringing in?
- Dave Baumgardner.

02:54.069 --> 02:56.068
"Bam-Bam."

02:56.071 --> 02:59.705
I served with him in Kandahar.
He'll do a good job.

02:59.708 --> 03:01.707
I'm happy to brief him if you'd like.

03:01.710 --> 03:03.709
For what it's worth... [sighs]

03:03.712 --> 03:06.478
Agent Christopher fought
like hell to keep you here.

03:06.481 --> 03:08.480
Thank you, ma'am.

03:08.483 --> 03:09.681
But I get it.

03:09.684 --> 03:11.049
It's results-oriented business,

03:11.052 --> 03:13.018
and I haven't delivered results.

03:13.021 --> 03:14.519
[overlapping chatter]

03:14.522 --> 03:16.588
<i>[exciting music]</i>

03:16.591 --> 03:20.258
- Attempting to pinpoint now.
- Level reading is satisfactory.

03:20.261 --> 03:22.094
- The states are moving.
- What's going on?

03:22.097 --> 03:23.161
Flynn's gone.

03:23.164 --> 03:25.998
To March 2, 1836.

03:26.001 --> 03:27.265
Looks like...

03:27.268 --> 03:28.435
around San Antonio.

03:28.437 --> 03:31.003
That's days before the Alamo.

03:31.006 --> 03:32.738
I'm from Tas. We all know that one.

03:32.741 --> 03:34.106
I'll call Lucy.

03:34.109 --> 03:35.374
When's Baumgardner gonna get here?

03:35.377 --> 03:36.775
Not soon enough.

03:36.778 --> 03:38.577
Looks like you're talking one more trip.

03:38.580 --> 03:39.947
I'll make the best of it ma'am.

03:39.949 --> 03:41.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:41.116 --> 03:43.348
No, yeah, I'm on my way.

03:43.351 --> 03:45.283
[cell phone beeps]

03:45.286 --> 03:47.287
- [sighs]
- Where are you going?

03:48.957 --> 03:51.723
- Work.
- At this hour?

03:51.726 --> 03:53.892
Lucy, what's so important
about this new job

03:53.895 --> 03:55.894
that these Mason Industries people

03:55.897 --> 03:57.062
need you to be there at midnight?

03:57.065 --> 03:58.559
Mom, I told you. I signed an NDA.

03:58.584 --> 04:00.532
- I can't talk about it.
- So I won't tell anyone.

04:00.535 --> 04:01.967
Come on. Just between you and me.

04:01.970 --> 04:03.535
It doesn't work that way, okay?

04:03.538 --> 04:05.971
- I gotta go.
- Lucy.

04:05.974 --> 04:08.073
I'm asking because I'm worried.

04:08.076 --> 04:09.408
You moved back in with me,

04:09.411 --> 04:10.876
you're ignoring your fiancé,

04:10.879 --> 04:12.711
and you are bailing on your teaching.

04:12.714 --> 04:14.246
I get how strange this all looks,

04:14.249 --> 04:16.648
and I do wish that I could
talk to you about it.

04:16.651 --> 04:18.116
But... [sighs]

04:18.119 --> 04:19.651
I just need you to undstand.

04:19.654 --> 04:21.286
We used to talk. Do you remember?

04:21.289 --> 04:23.088
So talk to me. Maybe I can help you.

04:23.091 --> 04:24.656
Okay, okay. Mom, please, all right?

04:24.659 --> 04:26.825
Because from where I am standing,

04:26.828 --> 04:29.628
you're throwing away everything
you've ever worked for,

04:29.631 --> 04:31.930
and for what?

04:31.933 --> 04:33.799
Lucy, I raised you better than that.

04:33.802 --> 04:35.333
I raised you to use your head,

04:35.336 --> 04:37.669
and that Lucy has her
whole life planned out.

04:37.672 --> 04:40.439
Well, maybe I'm not that
Lucy anymore, okay?

04:40.442 --> 04:42.025
- Really?
- And let's be honest.

04:42.050 --> 04:43.742
There's a lot you're not telling me either.

04:43.745 --> 04:45.143
Are we seriously gonna do this again?

04:45.146 --> 04:47.813
You won't even tell me his name.

04:47.816 --> 04:49.650
[sighs]

04:51.586 --> 04:53.985
I just wanna know who my father is.

04:53.988 --> 04:57.189
[soln music]

04:57.192 --> 04:58.523
[door opens]

04:58.526 --> 05:01.528
[overlapping chatter, alarm blaring]

05:01.530 --> 05:04.529
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

05:04.532 --> 05:05.597
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:05.600 --> 05:08.266
So, Alamo, huh?

05:08.269 --> 05:10.836
A word synonymous with
gory and inescapable death.

05:10.839 --> 05:13.171
Wyatt, you wanna say something
strong and reassuring?

05:13.174 --> 05:15.373
Hey, don't look at me. I just got fired.

05:15.376 --> 05:17.776
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:17.779 --> 05:19.277
- What?
- Yeah.

05:19.280 --> 05:20.879
This is gonna be my last mission.

05:20.882 --> 05:23.014
How'd you get fired?

05:23.017 --> 05:24.616
How do I get fired?

05:24.619 --> 05:26.017
[chuckles softly]

05:26.020 --> 05:28.019
I mean, you...
You seem pretty okay with this.

05:28.022 --> 05:29.988
Yeah, well, I know the
guy they're bringing in.

05:29.991 --> 05:32.390
He's good. You'll like him better than me.

05:32.393 --> 05:35.026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:35.029 --> 05:36.695
What if those go off in here?

05:36.698 --> 05:39.064
They won't. I know what I'm doing.

05:39.067 --> 05:40.899
Okay, but still.

05:40.902 --> 05:42.734
You're bringing grenades

05:42.737 --> 05:45.170
to the Alamo?

05:45.173 --> 05:46.505
Well...

05:46.508 --> 05:49.541
I get one last shot at Flynn...

05:49.544 --> 05:51.676
you better believe I'm gonna take it.

05:51.679 --> 05:53.578
What are they gonna do?

05:53.581 --> 05:55.580
Fire me?

05:55.583 --> 05:59.684
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:59.687 --> 06:02.689
[whirring and clanking]

06:04.025 --> 06:06.026
Quite something, isn't she?

06:07.929 --> 06:10.162
Normally I'm jealous
I'm not going with them.

06:10.165 --> 06:11.899
Not this time.

06:11.901 --> 06:13.365
Not this mission.

06:13.368 --> 06:16.868
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:16.871 --> 06:19.738
[papers rustling, alarm blaring]

06:19.741 --> 06:22.741
