07:52.753 --> 07:55.952
So are we just, like, walking into a war?

07:55.955 --> 07:58.721
Relax. It's not for another four days.

07:58.724 --> 08:01.424
When General Santa Anna
and his 4,000 troops

08:01.427 --> 08:03.726
kill 180 men in less than an hour.

08:03.729 --> 08:05.795
Right. I'll just relax.

08:05.798 --> 08:08.264
Hmm. But after they were overrun,

08:08.267 --> 08:09.832
the whole "Remember the Alamo" thing,

08:09.835 --> 08:11.167
it got everybody all fired up

08:11.170 --> 08:12.635
and it turned a small rebellion

08:12.638 --> 08:14.470
into a huge revolution overnight.

08:14.473 --> 08:17.607
I mean, this battle is why
there's even a state of Texas.

08:17.610 --> 08:19.609
A bunch of famous people died here too.

08:19.612 --> 08:21.778
Jim Bowie. The knife's named after him.

08:21.781 --> 08:22.979
Davy Crockett.

08:22.982 --> 08:24.681
So how do we get in?

08:24.684 --> 08:26.416
Right through the front door.

08:26.419 --> 08:28.017
Honestly, they're so undermanned

08:28.020 --> 08:29.519
they'll probably take
any help they can get.

08:29.522 --> 08:31.821
So what does Flynn want?

08:31.824 --> 08:35.124
I don't know. To make it worse, I guess?

08:35.126 --> 08:37.493
How the hell do you make the Alamo worse?

08:37.496 --> 08:40.496
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:40.499 --> 08:47.337
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:47.340 --> 08:50.342
[indistinct chatter]

08:55.181 --> 08:57.680
No, baby, you put the
kindling down here like this.

08:57.683 --> 08:58.881
See?

08:58.884 --> 09:01.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:01.187 --> 09:02.885
I expected soldiers.

09:02.888 --> 09:04.821
It's mostly local ranchers, farmers,

09:04.824 --> 09:05.988
families too.

09:05.991 --> 09:07.357
Part of me just wants to shout out

09:07.360 --> 09:09.627
- "run for your lives," you know?
- I know.

09:10.683 --> 09:12.628
- Are those, uh...
- Free men.

09:12.631 --> 09:14.897
Slavery was outlawed in Mexico,

09:14.900 --> 09:16.966
and this is all technically still Mexico.

09:16.969 --> 09:18.835
At least for one more month, anyway.

09:18.838 --> 09:20.570
- Viva la Mexico.
- [scoffs]

09:20.573 --> 09:23.506
[quietly] I wouldn't say
that too loud around here.

09:23.509 --> 09:25.343
That's gotta be him.

09:26.812 --> 09:28.411
That's Bowie.

09:28.414 --> 09:32.315
Um... let me take lead on this, okay?

09:32.318 --> 09:35.151
Excuse me, Colonel Bowie? Sir?

09:35.154 --> 09:36.819
- Yes, ma'am?
- Hello, hi.

09:36.822 --> 09:39.188
I'm... I'm Lucy Preston.
This is Wyatt Logan.

09:39.191 --> 09:40.823
- How do you do, sir?
- Wyatt.

09:40.826 --> 09:42.658
We just arrived. We're here to volunteer.

09:42.661 --> 09:44.494
Well, I'm glad to have you.

09:44.497 --> 09:46.396
So you're just in from where?

09:46.399 --> 09:48.765
The east. San Felipe.

09:48.768 --> 09:51.100
Ah, I've got family in San Felipe.

09:51.125 --> 09:52.503
Oh, you do?

09:52.528 --> 09:55.405
It's... it's nice. It's lovely there.

09:55.408 --> 09:57.106
Um... actually, I was...

09:57.109 --> 10:00.843
We, uh, were passing through
on the road from San Felipe...

10:00.846 --> 10:03.045
Look, we're looking for a guy.

10:03.048 --> 10:06.616
Tall guy, dark hair, accent,
name is Garcia Flynn.

10:06.619 --> 10:07.850
What? I'm sorry...

10:07.853 --> 10:09.123
He's a Mexican sympathizer.

10:09.148 --> 10:11.220
This guy might have
already infiltrated the fort.

10:11.223 --> 10:13.456
He is very dangerous. Have you seen him?

10:13.459 --> 10:15.358
I don't know...

10:15.361 --> 10:16.926
but I will ask around.

10:16.929 --> 10:18.428
Okay.

10:18.431 --> 10:21.264
- Ma'am.
- Thank you kindly.

10:21.267 --> 10:22.965
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:22.968 --> 10:24.500
You came on a little strong
with him, didn't you?

10:24.524 --> 10:25.935
I mean, I just don't want
you to freak him out.

10:25.938 --> 10:28.471
We don't have time to play cowboy.

10:28.474 --> 10:30.573
That bear was ten feet tall

10:30.576 --> 10:33.109
standing on his hind legs.

10:33.112 --> 10:35.478
I saw him coming, all I could think was,

10:35.481 --> 10:38.281
"I'm so skinny, I'm gonna
make piss-poor eating."

10:38.284 --> 10:39.415
[laughter]

10:39.418 --> 10:41.317
Davy Crockett.

10:41.320 --> 10:42.985
Guilty.

10:42.988 --> 10:45.388
- He's got the hat.
- [laughs]

10:45.391 --> 10:47.924
Come on. What happened then?

10:47.927 --> 10:50.259
Well, he roared and he lunged for me.

10:50.262 --> 10:52.295
I just grabbed him.

10:52.298 --> 10:55.064
That bear locked those
teeth around my arm,

10:55.067 --> 10:57.467
started chewing on it like
a turkey leg at Christmas.

10:57.470 --> 10:59.540
- [laughter]
- What'd you do then?

10:59.565 --> 11:01.571
Well, I wasn't gonna let
him finish his supper.

11:01.574 --> 11:03.739
- [laughter]
- I fought him off,

11:03.742 --> 11:05.308
then I wrestled him to the ground.

11:05.311 --> 11:07.076
- You wrestled him one-handed?
- Shut up, Johnny.

11:07.079 --> 11:08.644
- He's telling a story.
- Yeah, Johnny...

11:08.647 --> 11:10.112
[whispers] Oh, my God.

11:10.115 --> 11:12.448
- That's Davy Crockett.
- I know, right?

11:12.451 --> 11:14.984
We're not tourists.

11:14.987 --> 11:17.787
Split up. Scour every inch of this place.

11:17.790 --> 11:19.155
We gotta find Flynn. You got it?

11:19.158 --> 11:21.457
Yes, got it.

11:21.460 --> 11:23.960
[indistinct chatter]

11:23.963 --> 11:25.361
Ma'am.

11:25.364 --> 11:28.364
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:28.367 --> 11:35.373
