_

19:28.016 --> 19:31.016
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:31.019 --> 19:38.025
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:45.167 --> 19:48.167
[bugle playing]

19:48.170 --> 19:51.170
[indistinct shouting]

19:51.173 --> 19:58.043
♪ ♪

19:58.046 --> 20:01.147
What the hell's with the music?

20:01.172 --> 20:03.682
Oh, it's meant to keep us up at night.

20:03.685 --> 20:06.719
Me, I don't mind it.

20:06.722 --> 20:09.724
When the music stops,
that's when you gotta worry.

20:10.759 --> 20:13.359
Psychological warfare.

20:13.362 --> 20:15.461
Psycho-what?

20:15.464 --> 20:17.463
Nothing. [clears throat]

20:17.466 --> 20:20.733
♪ ♪

20:20.736 --> 20:21.994
[exhales]

20:22.019 --> 20:23.511
Don't suppose you know a way out of here?

20:23.535 --> 20:26.885
Sure. Main gate.

20:26.910 --> 20:30.075
3,000-man welcome committee
out there waiting for you.

20:30.078 --> 20:32.211
♪ ♪

20:32.214 --> 20:33.612
[gags]

20:33.615 --> 20:35.714
[coughing]

20:35.717 --> 20:38.085
[laughs]

20:38.110 --> 20:39.718
You thought that was water, did you?

20:39.721 --> 20:41.487
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

20:41.490 --> 20:43.656
There's more whiskey than water right now

20:43.659 --> 20:45.891
since Santa Anna blocked the aqueduct.

20:45.894 --> 20:47.493
There's an aqueduct?

20:47.496 --> 20:48.727
Yeah.

20:48.730 --> 20:50.729
Show me.

20:50.732 --> 20:52.832
Great news, the aqueduct goes

20:52.835 --> 20:55.000
from the fort to the river here.

20:55.003 --> 20:56.635
That's right, there was
an aqueduct system

20:56.638 --> 20:58.637
running all through this
area built in the 1740s.

20:58.640 --> 20:59.870
If we can get in, we can sneak

20:59.895 --> 21:01.106
the women and the children out.

21:01.109 --> 21:02.628
- Your letter too.
- Okay.

21:02.653 --> 21:05.110
The only problem is where it connects.

21:05.113 --> 21:07.479
Under the chapel
via a softball-sized hole

21:07.482 --> 21:09.114
through three feet of stone.

21:09.117 --> 21:12.284
So how the hell are we
supposed to get through that?

21:12.287 --> 21:14.286
I'm sorry, where's the great news here?

21:14.289 --> 21:15.855
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:15.858 --> 21:17.656
[exhales sharply]
How's the letter coming?

21:17.659 --> 21:19.625
[sighs] It's not.

21:19.628 --> 21:21.717
I'm having the world's worst
case of writer's block.

21:21.742 --> 21:23.963
I know that there's something about
"patriotism" and "liberty"

21:23.966 --> 21:25.798
and "American character."

21:25.801 --> 21:27.499
- I think.
- You don't know?

21:27.502 --> 21:29.435
- You're the historian.
- Yeah, believe it or not,

21:29.438 --> 21:31.170
I have not memorized every
single letter ever written

21:31.173 --> 21:32.805
in the history of time, and this letter,

21:32.808 --> 21:34.773
if I don't get every single
word exactly right...

21:34.776 --> 21:36.675
It's just a letter.

21:36.678 --> 21:38.110
It's not just a letter.

21:38.113 --> 21:39.845
It's the letter that created Texas.

21:39.848 --> 21:41.480
- No pressure or anything.
- For God sakes.

21:41.483 --> 21:43.215
You're in your own head.
Just write something.

21:43.218 --> 21:44.650
Anything. It doesn't have to be exact.

21:44.653 --> 21:45.784
Oh, I can just say whatever I want

21:45.787 --> 21:47.152
- like you did with Bowie?
- Yes.

21:47.155 --> 21:48.854
You say what's in here.

21:48.857 --> 21:50.778
Quit pretending.

21:50.803 --> 21:53.251
All this dress-up

21:53.254 --> 21:54.585
and the grade school drama

21:54.588 --> 21:56.153
and the "we're from San Felipe." I...

21:56.156 --> 21:57.522
That's the job. That's <i>my</i> job.

21:57.525 --> 21:59.423
No, the job is Flynn!

21:59.426 --> 22:02.260
And I cannot do it with all of this crap!

22:02.263 --> 22:04.962
[exhales sharply]
How am I supposed to do my job

22:04.965 --> 22:08.099
with my hands tied behind my back?

22:08.102 --> 22:09.700
[exhales sharply]

22:09.703 --> 22:13.704
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:13.707 --> 22:17.375
You know what, maybe
Agent Christopher was right.

22:17.378 --> 22:20.378
Maybe I'm not the guy for the job.

22:20.381 --> 22:22.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:22.283 --> 22:23.548
I'm sorry.

22:23.551 --> 22:24.822
Wyatt...

22:24.847 --> 22:26.651
[explosions]

22:26.654 --> 22:29.654
[indistinct shouting and screaming]

22:29.657 --> 22:32.657
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:32.660 --> 22:38.996
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:38.999 --> 22:41.198
[coughing]

22:41.201 --> 22:44.203
[shouting, explosions continue]

22:46.707 --> 22:48.506
[grunts]

22:48.509 --> 22:53.744
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:53.747 --> 22:55.146
Wyatt!

22:55.149 --> 22:58.149
- [coughing]
- [grunting]

22:58.152 --> 23:01.485
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:01.488 --> 23:04.388
Wyatt? [coughs]

23:04.391 --> 23:06.023
<i>[heart beating]</i>

23:06.026 --> 23:08.192
[exhales sharply]

23:08.195 --> 23:10.094
Come on, buddy. Help me out here.

23:10.097 --> 23:11.896
There you go. Pull your arm back.

23:11.899 --> 23:13.931
Here we go.

23:13.934 --> 23:16.267
- Bowie!
- Over here.

23:16.270 --> 23:17.768
[explosions continue]

23:17.771 --> 23:20.037
Here, give him to me. I got him.

23:20.040 --> 23:22.039
- You got him?
- Yeah, yeah.

23:22.042 --> 23:27.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:38.769 --> 23:40.967
Hey.

23:40.970 --> 23:44.571
You don't look so bad for
having a wall fall on you.

23:45.037 --> 23:46.502
Could have been worse.

23:46.505 --> 23:49.038
Could have been a whole building.

23:49.041 --> 23:52.043
Santa Anna's just softening us up.

23:55.047 --> 23:56.646
Almost finished.

23:56.649 --> 23:58.483
You're doing fine.

23:59.985 --> 24:04.186
How'd your old man raise
such a tough kid, huh?

24:04.189 --> 24:07.056
Wouldn't know.

24:07.059 --> 24:09.992
Santa Anna got him.

24:09.995 --> 24:11.894
Him and my brothers.

24:11.897 --> 24:13.898
Bexar last year.

24:18.337 --> 24:21.904
[grunting]

24:21.929 --> 24:24.274
Scouts just came back.

24:24.299 --> 24:26.208
Reported about another 1,000 troops

24:26.211 --> 24:28.210
just joined Santa Anna's party outside.

24:28.213 --> 24:30.713
The hell are you doing?

24:30.716 --> 24:32.682
Trying to get the women and children out.

24:32.685 --> 24:34.183
Through the aqueduct.

24:34.186 --> 24:36.552
Just gotta get through these first...

24:36.555 --> 24:38.020
three...

24:38.023 --> 24:40.389
feet.

24:40.392 --> 24:41.947
You know that's stone?

24:41.972 --> 24:43.993
I am aware!

24:43.996 --> 24:46.998
[panting]

24:53.772 --> 24:55.671
How do you do it?

24:55.674 --> 24:57.073
How are you not...

24:57.076 --> 25:00.176
screaming in terror right now?

25:00.179 --> 25:03.346
You're not screaming in terror.

25:03.349 --> 25:05.348
On the outside.

25:05.373 --> 25:08.136
You... you're, like, macho at
a level I can't even deal with.

25:08.161 --> 25:10.042
All "King of the Wild Frontier."

25:10.067 --> 25:13.069
You wrestled a bear, for God sakes.

25:13.792 --> 25:17.226
I never wrestled a bear.

25:17.251 --> 25:18.725
What?

25:18.750 --> 25:19.862
Not even close.

25:19.865 --> 25:21.230
But there was a bear.

25:21.233 --> 25:23.032
What happened?

25:23.035 --> 25:27.036
Well, I was out scouting, I got cornered,

25:27.039 --> 25:28.037
she charged me,

25:28.040 --> 25:32.041
and I pissed myself.

25:32.044 --> 25:35.244
Fired wild, and I fell into a creek.

25:35.247 --> 25:37.213
When I got myself up, I couldn't believe

25:37.216 --> 25:39.749
the shot took her down.

25:39.752 --> 25:41.617
I was scared outta my mind.

25:41.620 --> 25:43.419
Then what did you do?

25:43.422 --> 25:47.423
Well, I went back and told
my men that I wrestled a bear.

25:47.426 --> 25:49.125
One-handed.

25:49.128 --> 25:50.926
[chuckles]

25:50.929 --> 25:55.331
Because sometimes folks need
a leader who can wrestle a bear.

25:55.334 --> 25:58.334
<i>[solemn music]</i>

25:58.337 --> 26:00.836
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:00.839 --> 26:03.339
Now don't you go telling everybody

26:03.342 --> 26:05.841
and ruin my reputation.

26:05.844 --> 26:12.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:21.593 --> 26:24.126
So I-I appreciate you
pulling young John out

26:24.129 --> 26:25.795
from under that wall.

26:25.798 --> 26:28.964
You saved his life, you know.

26:28.967 --> 26:31.969
Anyone would have done the same.

26:33.772 --> 26:35.773
We're not gonna make it.

26:39.436 --> 26:42.711
Colonel Fannin and
his troops ain't coming.

26:42.714 --> 26:44.713
And Santa Anna's getting
his reinforcements

26:44.716 --> 26:48.451
like you said he would.

26:48.454 --> 26:50.619
Won't be long now.

26:50.622 --> 26:53.322
Look, I don't like being right.

26:53.325 --> 26:55.191
I'd give anything to get
your men out of this.

26:55.194 --> 26:57.626
I just don't know how.

26:57.629 --> 26:59.228
But I'm pretty sure

26:59.231 --> 27:01.697
that I could help save the
women and the children.

27:01.700 --> 27:04.702
You want to get them out
through the aqueduct, don't you?

27:06.338 --> 27:08.137
Crockett saw your man

27:08.140 --> 27:11.373
banging away on the stone.

27:11.376 --> 27:13.576
Rufus will figure it out.

27:13.579 --> 27:16.712
But we gotta buy him the time.

27:16.715 --> 27:19.717
[sighs] Well, you better tell me how.

27:24.857 --> 27:27.923
Here's the fort.

27:27.926 --> 27:30.759
Now, Santa Anna's men

27:30.762 --> 27:33.429
are coming over these
walls, like it or not.

27:33.432 --> 27:35.531
And if they come over all at once,

27:35.534 --> 27:37.199
it's gonna be over fast.

27:37.202 --> 27:39.201
Maybe too fast.

27:39.204 --> 27:42.204
So I want you to pull your
men off the north wall.

27:42.207 --> 27:44.073
Leave it undefended.

27:44.076 --> 27:46.609
The north wall's our weakest wall.

27:46.612 --> 27:50.913
Exactly, that's where you
want Santa Anna to attack.

27:50.916 --> 27:53.115
Your soldiers won't be
getting hit on all four sides.

27:53.118 --> 27:55.217
Instead, you'll bottle-neck 'em
right through here.

27:55.220 --> 27:58.621
This won't stop 'em.

27:58.624 --> 28:00.623
But it'll slow 'em down.

28:00.626 --> 28:03.058
Hopefully long enough to
get the civilians out.

28:03.061 --> 28:05.062
You done this before.

28:07.633 --> 28:10.635
Haven't you? Where?

28:12.404 --> 28:14.937
Nowhere near here.

28:14.940 --> 28:18.240
It was kind of like this, though.

28:18.243 --> 28:20.876
We were pinned down.

28:20.879 --> 28:23.281
Outmanned. Outgunned.

28:25.083 --> 28:28.085
I'm the only one that made it out.

28:31.056 --> 28:33.656
Your men...

28:33.659 --> 28:36.992
they last long?

28:36.995 --> 28:40.162
Wish I knew.

28:40.165 --> 28:43.165
I left them behind.

28:43.168 --> 28:46.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:46.138 --> 28:47.770
One of us had to get this important piece

28:47.773 --> 28:49.004
of intelligence out.

28:49.007 --> 28:51.407
So...

28:51.410 --> 28:54.810
we flipped a damn coin.

28:54.813 --> 28:56.845
It was between me and my buddy Zachary.

28:56.848 --> 28:59.615
We were the only two not wounded.

28:59.618 --> 29:02.251
I'm the jerk that had to call heads.

29:02.254 --> 29:04.253
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:04.256 --> 29:07.323
Zach... [chuckles]

29:07.326 --> 29:09.325
He said I was meant to survive.

29:09.328 --> 29:10.826
You know, like it was fate.

29:10.829 --> 29:13.963
As if that's a thing.

29:13.966 --> 29:17.099
So six men...

29:17.102 --> 29:19.602
held off a hundred fighters,

29:19.605 --> 29:22.004
so I could escape.

29:22.007 --> 29:23.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:23.775 --> 29:26.775
I left them there to die.

29:26.778 --> 29:30.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:30.382 --> 29:33.382
And they gave me a medal for it.

29:33.385 --> 29:40.391
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:42.127 --> 29:44.128
Crockett.

29:45.998 --> 29:49.198
Pull all our men, the cannon,

29:49.201 --> 29:52.201
everything off the north wall.

29:52.204 --> 29:54.370
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:54.373 --> 29:57.006
We're gonna try and get
the women and children out.

29:57.009 --> 30:03.212
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:03.215 --> 30:06.217
[indistinct chatter]

30:07.219 --> 30:14.225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:15.994 --> 30:18.994
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:18.997 --> 30:22.865
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:22.868 --> 30:25.234
<i>When I was young, I'd read stories</i>

30:25.237 --> 30:27.670
<i>about great heroes doing great deeds.</i>

30:27.673 --> 30:29.438
<i>The truth is,</i>

30:29.441 --> 30:32.941
<i>real heroes don't look
at all like I pictured.</i>

30:32.944 --> 30:35.210
<i>- They're far from perfect.</i>
- Here.

30:35.213 --> 30:37.780
<i>Bull-headed, stubborn, reckless.</i>

30:37.783 --> 30:41.450
<i>And also recklessly brave.</i>

30:41.453 --> 30:44.687
<i>They charge in without a
thought to themselves.</i>

30:44.690 --> 30:47.122
<i>Not without fear or doubt,</i>

30:47.125 --> 30:48.891
<i>but in spite of it.</i>

30:48.894 --> 30:51.393
<i>We are all scared.</i>

30:51.396 --> 30:53.762
<i>But we are going to fight and die anyway,</i>

30:53.765 --> 30:56.799
<i>to give everyone else a
chance at a better future.</i>

30:56.802 --> 30:59.068
<i>Because the future matters.</i>

30:59.071 --> 31:00.769
<i>Victory or death.</i>

31:00.772 --> 31:05.541
<i>Signed, the men and women of the Alamo.</i>

31:05.544 --> 31:08.544
[distant patriotic music]

31:08.547 --> 31:15.553
♪ ♪

31:17.255 --> 31:18.972
I should have thought of this before.

31:18.997 --> 31:20.366
Thought of what?

31:20.391 --> 31:22.991
Do you still have those grenades?

31:23.016 --> 31:25.017
Um...

31:28.133 --> 31:31.133
[men shouting]

31:31.136 --> 31:34.136
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

31:34.139 --> 31:36.438
<i>♪</i>

31:36.441 --> 31:38.841
Here we go.

31:38.844 --> 31:45.483
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:50.079 --> 31:53.047
[men shouting]

31:55.283 --> 31:57.282
[all shouting]

31:57.285 --> 32:00.886
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

32:00.889 --> 32:03.789
Come on.

32:03.792 --> 32:05.190
Aah!

32:05.193 --> 32:07.592
[indistinct shouting]

32:07.595 --> 32:08.727
Wait.

32:08.730 --> 32:11.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:11.132 --> 32:12.397
Where are they?

32:12.400 --> 32:14.433
Wait for the order.

32:14.436 --> 32:21.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:26.548 --> 32:28.780
[indistinct shouting]

32:28.783 --> 32:31.783
[horses galloping]

32:31.786 --> 32:32.918
Fire!

32:32.921 --> 32:33.986
[gunfire]

32:33.989 --> 32:36.621
[men yelping]

32:36.624 --> 32:40.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:40.628 --> 32:43.628
[explosions and gunfire]

32:43.631 --> 32:45.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:45.633 --> 32:48.635
[indistinct shouting]

32:51.006 --> 32:54.139
- Aah!
- [horse whinnies]

32:54.142 --> 32:55.741
Damn it, Rufus, hurry up.

32:55.744 --> 32:58.744
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:58.747 --> 33:05.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:07.522 --> 33:08.589
[whispers to self]

33:12.060 --> 33:15.060
[men shouting]

33:15.063 --> 33:18.697
You're okay. You're okay.

33:18.700 --> 33:20.399
Let's go. We got our way out.

33:20.402 --> 33:22.501
Thank God.

33:22.504 --> 33:23.668
Okay.

33:23.671 --> 33:25.871
Come on. Come on.

33:25.874 --> 33:27.973
Okay, everybody follow him.

33:27.976 --> 33:29.574
Follow him where?

33:29.577 --> 33:31.209
Uh, to the chapel.

33:31.212 --> 33:32.677
You'll be able to get
out through the aqueduct.

33:32.680 --> 33:33.879
Hurry.

33:33.882 --> 33:35.080
I need you to be brave, sweetheart.

33:35.083 --> 33:36.314
Don't let go of my hand, okay?

33:36.317 --> 33:38.683
[gunfire outside]

33:38.686 --> 33:40.919
Here, take this.

33:40.922 --> 33:42.320
I'll get Wyatt.

33:42.323 --> 33:45.057
Let's go.

33:45.060 --> 33:47.192
[gunfire]

33:47.195 --> 33:50.395
[men grunting and shouting]

33:50.398 --> 33:53.367
[gunfire]

33:54.569 --> 33:57.702
<i>[tense music]</i>

33:57.705 --> 34:01.106
<i>[heart beating]</i>

34:01.109 --> 34:03.075
Oh!

34:03.078 --> 34:04.076
Wyatt.

34:04.079 --> 34:05.077
Lucy?

34:05.080 --> 34:06.278
Rufus did it.

34:06.281 --> 34:07.679
[gunfire]

34:07.682 --> 34:10.014
There's a way out. Come on, let's go.

34:10.018 --> 34:11.083
Aah!

34:11.085 --> 34:14.085
[gunfire]

34:14.089 --> 34:16.221
We have to go. Now.

34:16.224 --> 34:17.589
[gunfire]

34:17.592 --> 34:18.857
Wyatt?

34:18.860 --> 34:20.257
Wyatt.

34:20.261 --> 34:23.862
[gunfire]

34:23.864 --> 34:25.764
I'm not going.

34:25.766 --> 34:28.100
What? No.

34:28.103 --> 34:29.935
- What do you mean?
- You don't need me.

34:29.938 --> 34:31.536
They're getting rid of me anyway, right?

34:31.539 --> 34:33.138
You can't stay here. Everybody dies.

34:33.141 --> 34:34.773
No, I know.

34:34.775 --> 34:37.409
I can't leave good me
like this, not again.

34:37.411 --> 34:41.079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:41.081 --> 34:43.915
No. No, Wyatt.

34:43.918 --> 34:46.150
What difference does it make?

34:46.154 --> 34:48.152
Jessica, everyone I care about is gone.

34:48.156 --> 34:49.955
[gunfire continues]

34:49.958 --> 34:52.090
Let me do one good thing.

34:52.092 --> 34:54.458
Let me buy you the time to get out.

34:54.462 --> 34:56.460
What about us? We're counting on you.

34:56.464 --> 34:57.896
The next guy's gonna handle it.

34:57.899 --> 34:59.564
I don't want anybody else.

34:59.567 --> 35:01.666
Look, I trust you.

35:01.669 --> 35:03.602
You are the one that I trust.

35:03.605 --> 35:05.604
Rufus needs you. I need you.

35:05.607 --> 35:07.305
Okay?

35:07.308 --> 35:10.310
[gunfire]

35:12.080 --> 35:15.480
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:15.483 --> 35:16.615
Get ready to run.

35:16.618 --> 35:18.450
Okay.

35:18.453 --> 35:21.920
Just stay low.
It goes straight to the river.

35:21.923 --> 35:23.455
Keep your head down.

35:23.458 --> 35:27.459
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:27.462 --> 35:28.627
What took you so long?

35:28.630 --> 35:31.196
John, watch the door.

35:31.199 --> 35:33.167
Give him the gun.

35:35.370 --> 35:38.770
You're not John Smith by
any chance, are you?

35:38.773 --> 35:40.472
- Travis's messenger?
- Yes, ma'am.

35:40.475 --> 35:42.440
[gunfire outside]

35:42.443 --> 35:44.009
I need you to come with us.

35:44.012 --> 35:45.610
You have to deliver this
letter to General Houston.

35:45.613 --> 35:46.811
No, I'm not going anywhere, ma'am.

35:46.814 --> 35:47.946
- No, you have to.
- [door opens]

35:47.949 --> 35:49.447
[gunfire]

35:49.450 --> 35:52.284
We're completely overrun.

35:52.287 --> 35:53.685
We can't hold 'em off much longer.

35:53.688 --> 35:54.986
We almost got 'em all out.

35:54.989 --> 35:57.489
You all need to hightail it now.

35:57.492 --> 35:58.924
You gotta come with us.

35:58.927 --> 36:00.492
You just be sure to tell everybody

36:00.495 --> 36:02.861
I fought off a thousand of 'em.

36:02.864 --> 36:05.564
One-handed. Get.

36:05.567 --> 36:08.233
He has to take this
letter to General Houston.

36:08.236 --> 36:10.502
John Smith is gonna be the first mayor

36:10.505 --> 36:12.037
of San Antonio. He has to take it.

36:12.040 --> 36:15.008
[gunfire continues outside]

36:17.712 --> 36:19.844
- You have to deliver this.
- The hell I do.

36:19.847 --> 36:21.746
I'm not gonna leave the
only family I have left.

36:21.749 --> 36:25.016
I get it. Believe me.

36:25.019 --> 36:27.385
Sometimes the hardest thing in the world

36:27.388 --> 36:29.354
is to do the job.

36:29.357 --> 36:31.523
To be the only one to have to leave.

36:31.526 --> 36:34.859
But you have to.

36:34.862 --> 36:36.695
Those are the orders.

36:36.698 --> 36:39.731
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

36:39.734 --> 36:46.707
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:49.844 --> 36:51.676
- Yes, sir.
- Come on.

36:51.679 --> 36:54.279
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:54.282 --> 36:55.380
Come on. Watch the leg.

36:55.383 --> 36:57.916
Come here. I got you.

36:57.919 --> 36:59.918
- Go.
- Come on.

36:59.921 --> 37:02.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:02.390 --> 37:04.389
Thank you.

37:04.392 --> 37:11.365
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:13.534 --> 37:15.533
No.

37:15.536 --> 37:18.570
Don't ask me to leave.

37:18.573 --> 37:20.572
I can't leave my people.

37:20.575 --> 37:22.574
I can't leave mine.

37:22.577 --> 37:24.177
[chuckles softly]

37:26.447 --> 37:28.448
Hey, Sergeant.

37:36.057 --> 37:38.256
Can't let them have it now, can I?

37:38.259 --> 37:40.258
[gunfire continues outside]

37:40.261 --> 37:42.761
[banging]

37:42.764 --> 37:44.996
I can promise you

37:44.999 --> 37:47.165
that you won't die for nothing here.

37:47.168 --> 37:53.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:54.312 --> 37:57.078
[all shouting]

38:01.529 --> 38:03.660
The men, including Davy Crockett

38:03.663 --> 38:05.796
and Jim Bowie, were killed.

38:05.799 --> 38:07.230
But the women and children escaped,

38:07.233 --> 38:09.232
and the word of the Alamo inspired Texas

38:09.235 --> 38:11.735
to rise up and defeat Santa Anna.

38:11.738 --> 38:13.737
And the fact that we even know that...

38:13.762 --> 38:15.508
Means your letter got out.

38:15.533 --> 38:17.899
That must have been one hell of a letter.

38:17.902 --> 38:21.736
I'll say.

38:21.739 --> 38:25.540
I gather that Flynn is still out there.

38:25.543 --> 38:28.543
Yes, but he did have a very large army

38:28.546 --> 38:29.811
at his back this time.

38:29.814 --> 38:31.279
You're relieved of duty.

38:31.282 --> 38:32.413
You can report to your commanding officer

38:32.416 --> 38:33.881
for reassignment.

38:33.884 --> 38:35.650
- Yes, sir.
- Master Sergeant Baumgardner

38:35.653 --> 38:36.884
is in the waiting room,

38:36.887 --> 38:37.919
where he is about to learn

38:37.922 --> 38:39.387
that time travel is real.

38:39.390 --> 38:42.990
No, just... Just hold on.

38:42.993 --> 38:45.993
<i>[tense music]</i>

38:45.996 --> 38:48.262
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:48.265 --> 38:50.164
- You can't replace Wyatt.
- Lucy.

38:50.167 --> 38:51.632
We're the ones out
there risking our lives.

38:51.635 --> 38:53.968
I trust him... he makes
the right choice every time.

38:53.971 --> 38:57.438
- I won't do it without him.
- <i>We</i> won't do it without him.

38:57.441 --> 38:59.173
- Rufus.
- I know I'm just supposed

38:59.176 --> 39:02.343
to shut up and cooperate, but I can't.

39:02.346 --> 39:05.580
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:05.583 --> 39:07.815
I won't.

39:07.818 --> 39:09.917
Rufus is our only pilot, sir.

39:09.920 --> 39:13.154
Without him...

39:13.157 --> 39:15.990
What you've done to deserve this,
I can't imagine.

39:15.993 --> 39:17.592
So he can stay?

39:17.595 --> 39:19.594
Seems you gave us no choice.

39:19.597 --> 39:26.603
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:34.645 --> 39:36.646
[door opens]

39:41.218 --> 39:43.885
So?

39:43.888 --> 39:46.821
Let's have it.

39:46.824 --> 39:48.825
Are we gonna fight every day now?

40:01.472 --> 40:03.070
No.

40:03.073 --> 40:04.906
<i>[poignant music]</i>

40:04.909 --> 40:06.340
I don't want to fight anymore.

40:06.343 --> 40:09.544
Oh, Lucy.

40:09.547 --> 40:11.679
Life's too short.

40:11.682 --> 40:17.885
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:17.888 --> 40:19.820
I was a junior.

40:19.823 --> 40:22.823
And he was...

40:22.826 --> 40:24.258
well, he was a professor,

40:24.261 --> 40:26.227
if you really want to know the truth.

40:26.230 --> 40:29.564
He loved to argue.

40:29.567 --> 40:32.900
And he was handsome.

40:32.903 --> 40:35.069
He wanted to go into politics.

40:35.072 --> 40:37.905
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:37.908 --> 40:40.074
And then I told him I was pregnant.

40:40.077 --> 40:41.742
What did he say?

40:41.745 --> 40:43.711
You know, all the things
that he was supposed to.

40:43.714 --> 40:45.513
Back then that's what you did.

40:45.516 --> 40:47.915
But I didn't want to marry him.

40:47.918 --> 40:50.718
Hell, I barely even knew him.

40:50.721 --> 40:54.388
So we fought and I told
him I didn't need his help,

40:54.391 --> 40:55.923
and... [sighs]

40:55.926 --> 40:59.527
I haven't heard from him since.

40:59.530 --> 41:02.730
And, Lucy, I have no regrets.

41:02.733 --> 41:04.599
None.

41:04.602 --> 41:08.603
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.606 --> 41:11.272
And this is his name.

41:11.275 --> 41:18.281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:23.087 --> 41:26.754
Bam-Bam. Hold up.

41:26.757 --> 41:30.658
Wyatt Logan. What are you doing here?

41:30.661 --> 41:32.059
Heard you were stealing our oxygen.

41:32.062 --> 41:33.394
[chuckles]

41:33.397 --> 41:35.229
Well, they dragged me up from Pendleton,

41:35.232 --> 41:37.398
won't tell me crap,
and now they're flying me back.

41:37.401 --> 41:39.000
I don't suppose you know what's going on.

41:39.003 --> 41:40.501
What do you think?

41:40.504 --> 41:42.670
I figured the fact that you're here

41:42.673 --> 41:44.472
mean this whole thing is seriously fubar.

41:44.475 --> 41:47.241
- [chuckles]
- It's good seeing you.

41:47.244 --> 41:49.577
You too.

41:49.580 --> 41:51.812
Hey, when are you coming back to base?

41:51.815 --> 41:53.581
We're prepping for an op right now.

41:53.584 --> 41:55.016
It's the real deal.

41:55.019 --> 41:57.184
Robbie's there, Matty, all the boys.

41:57.187 --> 41:59.754
You'd love it.

41:59.757 --> 42:03.290
Yeah, I think I'll be here for a while.

42:03.293 --> 42:05.294
I got a new team.

42:05.319 --> 42:09.760
